&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational Occupational Therapist - Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a vacancy on our newly expanded Band 5 Rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This rotation contains both community and acute based options. There is a variety of posts which will encourage development of core OT skills within a supportive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotations include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute Admissions Unit &amp; Frailty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute Medical Wards (including Cardiac and Respiratory)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trauma and Orthopaedics (including some general surgery)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elderly Care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stroke&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A&amp;E&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working a well-established therapy teams, as part of a multi-disciplinary team, in the vibrant and diverse area of Lewisham.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong focus on teaching and development, including weekly in-service training, protected CPD time and a self-directed band 5 development group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our well established team will support your transition from student to newly qualified therapist or encourage further development for experienced band 5s&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working in Therapies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Tilley ( Lead Occupational Therapist ) emma.tilley1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
